rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of the week is going to go well. I plan on continuing to work throughout the recovery of COVID-19. I plan on going to restaurants while maintaining social distancing with my friends. I am going to exercise more often by jogging around the neighboorhood. Overall, my week will be productive.
critical_positive: I think what worked well with the conversation is that we had similar views around COVID-19. We spoke about the efficacy of vaccines, the mandates of wearing a mask out in public, and the goal to protect others from spreading the virus. I think it was great to hear someone echo your own sentiments like my partner did.
critical_negative: I think what didn't work well is that there were moments where I felt the conversation was forced. Nerves may have contributed to the conversation. There were times where I felt like I had to ask questions to keep the conversation going and my partner did a lot of the talking and I did most of the listening.

rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of the week will go very similar to others. A whole lot of nothing but staying home, watching tv, playing with my girls and taking some surveys. With any luck I will get a riding lesson and be able to take my girls to the pool.
critical_positive: We were both ready and willing to have a conversation. We wanted to get each other's opinions on the Cvid-19 and while we might have liked to talk about other things that really is the most pressing thing. I think we were both interested to learn what it's like in our respective states and how different it is.
critical_negative: I think the only challenge with the conversation really was that he had more schooling and was more advanced in his thinking so I felt a little self-conscious. He asked me how it worked and since I had done this before at least I knew what to do, but after that he really took over the conversation. IT was slightly off putting, but not a deal breaker
